1. boiler plate.
2. head tag:- title, links, css
3. body:- 
4. self closing tags:- 
    hr:- horizontal ruler,
    br:- line break,
    img:- src attribute:- link of image, alt attribut:- describe the image.
5. comments:- main content is visible after content in body text get parsed, if you do not want any text to get parsed. use comments:- <!---comment--->
6. headings in html:- h1 -> h2 -> h3 -> h4 -> h5 -> h6
7. paragraph tag:- to write paragraph
8. anchor tag:- to open a link of wny web page. target attributes tells us address of opening web page.
9. attributes:- style attribute :- to syle element, we can write css inside it
10. list :- ordered <ol>, unordered <ul>, <li>
11. tables:- <ta> table, <tr> table row, <th> table heading, <td> table data
12. forms:- <form> , input tag can be used to take input, in text, phone, gmail types, for larger texts you can use text area, for submitting button tag, checkboxes, radio buttons
13. as it is text:- pre tag <pre>
14. source code:- <code>
15. formatting:- bold <b>, italic <i>, underline <u>, Em <em>
16. Elements:- inline :- embedded elements <img>, <link> and block element :- new line <div>.
17. ids and classes:- to target specific elements and areas.
18. embed tag :- for embedding images.
19. css flexbox:- flex container :- parent activates itslef using display : flex; direct child are flex elements